result.execSummary:
The defendant William C. Drewek was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Possession of Firearm by Felon, a class G felony, Wisconsin Statutes 941.29(2).

Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

Court calls 14CF172 & 17CM164  @ 10:00 am.  Defendant William C. Drewek in court, in custody with attorney Jessica L Schuster.  Elizabeth R. Constable appeared for the State of Wisconsin. State has received revocation packet and reviewed and no corrections.  Atty Schuster has received revocation packet and reviewed and no corrections. Joint recommendation reached.  State gives agreement 17CM164 ct 1 plea, DRI ct 2 & 3, ct 4 plea, 14CF172 12 months jail, 45 days credit, 17CM164, 3 months jail, concurrent to each other  but consecutive to 14CF172, 2 days credit, costs, DNA Sample already completed. Atty Schuster and def. agree to plea agreement. Plea questionnaire and waiver of rights filed.  Def. understands charge and penalties. 17CM164 Ct 1 Poss of THC repeater, no contest plea, Ct 4 Child Neglect, no contest plea.  Court grants DRI in Ct 2 & 3. Def. advised of constitutional rights & J.T. rights. Def. understands elements. Def. admits prior conviction. Atty Schuster is satisfied.  Court finds pleas are freely & voluntarily given.  Factual basis.  Court finds factual basis, accept pleas and finds def. Guilty  Ct 1 Poss of THC repeater, Ct 4 Child Neglect. State gives statement. Atty Schuster gives statement.  Def. makes statement. Court orders on  14CF172 Ct 1 12 months jail, 45 days credit, huber privileges, Outstanding obligations convert to civil judgment
17CM164 ct 1 3 months jail, huber privileges, consecutive to 14CF172, costs, 200 DNA surcharge, No DNA Sample already provided, 2 days credit
ct 4 3 months jail, concurrent to Ct 1, Consecutive to 14CF172, Credit for 2 days, costs, waive DNA surcharge.  Def. given p.p. 1st payment due after month after released, 50 a month
